    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-01-11T08:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-01-11T08:30:00-05:00" n="274"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">888.2553/1–1153: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 274<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran (<persName corresp="#p_HLW1"
                            type="from">Henderson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d274fn1">Also sent to London eyes only for the Ambassador
                        and <persName corresp="#p_BHA1">Byroade</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-01-11T17:00:00+03:30"
                            >January 11, 1953—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2651. Eyes only Secretary and <persName corresp="#p_JJD1"
                    >Jernegan</persName>.</p>
                <pb facs="0629" n="603" xml:id="pg_603"/>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <p>Re paragraphs 3 and 5 Department’s 4599 to London, January 10 repeated
                            Tehran 1684, I have already set forth my views re possible tie-in of
                            monthly installments of commencement commercial negotiation in <gloss
                                target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 2634 to Department, January 10,
                            repeated London 852.<note n="2" xml:id="d274fn2">See <ref
                                    target="#d272fn5">footnote 5, Document 272</ref>.</note> If
                            Department and British not satisfied suggestion contained therein, our
                            first alternative might be to include in package agreement a letter
                            addressed by Dr. <persName corresp="#p_MM1">Mosadeq</persName>
                            preferably to me stating substantially as follows: <quote
                                rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Following the entry into force of its contract with <gloss
                                        target="#t_DMPA1">DMPA</gloss>, the <gloss target="#t_NIOC1"
                                        >NIOC</gloss> will be prepared to enter into negotiations
                                    with the International Export Company, in which the <gloss
                                        target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss> may be a participant, looking
                                    toward a contract of agreement for the <gloss target="#t_NIOC1"
                                        >NIOC</gloss> to sell to the International Export Company a
                                    definite amount of crude oil and oil products annually over a
                                    fixed period of years. The <gloss target="#t_NIOC1">NIOC</gloss>
                                    will enter into these negotiations just as soon as the
                                    International Export Company is prepared to open them”.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>As alternative to second sentence, following might be substituted: <quote
                                rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Such negotiations shall begin within 30 days after the <gloss
                                        target="#t_NIOC1">NIOC</gloss> agreement with <gloss
                                        target="#t_DMPA1">DMPA</gloss> has gone into effect. If for
                                    any reason International Export Company would not be ready to
                                    enter into negotiations within the 30 day period, the <gloss
                                        target="#t_NIOC1">NIOC</gloss> would be prepared to enter
                                    into such negotiations when the International Export Company is
                                    ready.” (See paragraph 2, <gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                                        >Embtel</gloss> 2608 to Department, January 8, repeated
                                    London 838.)<note n="3" xml:id="d274fn3">See <ref
                                            target="#d272fn3">footnote 3, Document 272</ref>.</note>
                                </p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <p>If above suggestions are entirely unsatisfactory, Department might care
                            to rephrase draft in paragraph 3 memo heads of agreement of <gloss
                                target="#t_DMPA1">DMPA</gloss> contract outlined in <gloss
                                target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 1588, December 31, to
                                Tehran.<note n="4" xml:id="d274fn4">Not printed.
                                (888.2553/12–3152)</note> That paragraph could read substantially as
                            follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“It is understood that following the entry into force of this
                                    contract, the <gloss target="#t_NIOC1">NIOC</gloss> will be
                                    prepared to enter into negotiations with the International
                                    Export Company in which the <gloss target="#t_NIOC1"
                                        >NIOC</gloss> may be participant, looking toward a contract
                                    of agreement for the <gloss target="#t_NIOC1">NIOC</gloss> to
                                    sell to the International Export Company a definite amount of
                                    crude oil and oil products annually over a fixed period of
                                    years, just as soon as the International Export Company is ready
                                    to enter into such negotiations.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Alternative to this could be similar to alternative in number 1
                            above.</p>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>I have no comments to make with remainder of telegram except that
                        Department might desire as suggested above to make certain changes in
                        heading number 3 in text of memo heads agreement incorporated in <gloss
                            target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 1588 to Tehran.</item>
                    <pb facs="0630" n="604" xml:id="pg_604"/>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>I hope that draft of terms of reference and other provisions of
                        arbitration agreement will be simple and as free as possible from
                        complicated legal language and follow wording <persName corresp="#p_MM1"
                            >Mosadeq</persName> so far as technically possible.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>Query: Are we certain that we wish to charge as much as 4½ percent
                        interest on loan to government-owner company? Would <gloss target="#t_DMPA1"
                            >DMPA</gloss> be violating regulations or setting undesirable precedents
                        by charging 3½ percent? Is interest to be paid in dollars or additional
                        oil?</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HLW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Henderson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
